description:
Next, we take a look into the life of William Tyndale, the translator of the English Bible. Voted as the 26th top Briton of all time on a BBC poll, William Tyndale sits comfortably amongst the most significant reformers. As a scholar and Bible translator in the 16th century, he had a lasting impact on Britain and Europe shaping the English language and left a lasting legacy long past the premature end to his life.

To find out more information about William Tyndale visit our website to read our extended article.
